<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
==Intersection Objects==
</div>

Wir müssen die gewünschten Querschnitte von ihren Achsen nach außen gehend festlegen und sie dann rotieren, um Objekte zu erstellen, die mit den Ergebnissen aus den vorherigen Schritten verschnitten werden, um ein richtiges Kegelradpaar zu ergeben.

<span id="Revolution_Object_1"></span>
===Drehkörper 1===

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Activate the first body ('''Body''').
# Create another [[Image:Sketcher_NewSketch.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_NewSketch|sketch]], and in the sketch:
## Project the lines representing the pitch diameters of our first sketch into our new sketch.
## Draw a construction line from their intersection point to the origin (his is where the pitch cones meet).
## Draw a closed wire of six straight lines:
##* One collinear with the vertical sketch axis,
##* two parallel to the horizontal projection line to define position and thickness of the hub area,
##* two lines perpendicular to the construction line, one running through the intersection point, that define the width of the teeth,
##* one line closing the wire that is only required to run outside the raw bevel gear since it already has a correctly modeled teeth hight.
# Leave the sketch.
# Create another new [[Image:PartDesign_Body.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_Body|PartDesign Body]] ('''Body003''').
# Use a [[Image:PartDesign_SubShapeBinder.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_SubShapeBinder|Sub-Shape Binder]] to copy the sketch into the body.
# Create a [[Image:PartDesign_Revolution.svg|16px]] [[PartDesign_Revolution|Revolve]] object ('''Revolution''') from the sub-shape binder.
</div>

